        "_account_id": 805,
        "name": "Neil Brown",
        "email": "neil@brown.name",
        "username": "neilbrown"
      },
      "date": "2020-09-25 11:02:38.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nI hit the bug in testing - twice.\nThe symptom is that the client stopped, waiting for the server.  The server has one thread constantly busy and getting soft-lockup warnings a couple of times a minute.\nI suspect it is much more likely to cause problems on a single-core host as nothing else can happen when one thread it locked up.\n\nI'll add the Fixes line, thanks for the reminder.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
